social_posts.post_text: Wallpaper from @lovevsdesign that you can customize with color and text. There are so many designs to pick from. It’s easy to install and remove without any damage. Sloane picked a simple design for her room and loves it! Peel and stick, yes please. I chose Handmade Scallop Wallpaper in Ceramic and Light!
I took some “me” time and went to get microneedling done by Lexie @luminescence_lex over at @cloverskinbar. And bonus for you, she is taking new clients. I have more in my stories too, check it out.

That’s a wrap to 2022. What a year and what amazing clients I had. I still am so grateful for everyone that puts their trust in me and continues to do so. Looking forward to 2023 and what work has for me. 🤟🏼

Balboa Island, CA May 2023. Last week for Ryan’s birthday we headed down to Balboa Island for some sun and sand. We didn’t get much sun, but it was still the perfect getaway with the family. We rode bikes, ate way too much @sanchostacos, shopped and was able to reconnect without work and school distractions. I’ve been thinking a lot about social media and just how my heart hasn’t been into it like it used to. I think every other post is an ad and if you’re not doing reels are you even being “seen”? I started this account as a way to connect with other moms of small kids, showcase my commercial work and share things that I was interested in, but now I don’t know. I’m in this rut. My kids don’t care to necessarily share all their happenings on this and I 100% respect that. Am I the only one that has this love/hate relationship with @instagram? I guess what I’m saying is it’s not what it used to be, more organic. Anyway… I won’t stop posting my stagnant pictures and I’ll throw in a reel here and there and probably share my workouts and health journey… maybe I do still connect with others and I just need to look harder. 🫶🏼

We had a lot of highs and a lot of lows this year. I’m trying to focus on the highs and savor all those moments, like the clips in this video. I also can’t sugar coat that life is all peachy. Just like so many others, I dealt with a lot of hard things. Loss of friendships, issues in marriage, sickness and most recently the loss of our precious nephew to suicide. 🕊️ I have learned a lot about myself this year and that I can come out stronger on the other side. I just hope that those struggling know they are not alone. I am here for you. There is so much love and kindness, we need to show it more to others. 🫶🏼

Not even sure how I can put this past weekend into words… We celebrated Braden and his life and what he has given to each one of us. I hate that his life was cut so short. I hate that it was suicide that took his life. I hate seeing his family suffer. Tanya (his mom) said it perfectly, her heart has never been so full and empty at the same time. There has been an incredible amount of love and support from all over, people that didn’t even know him but maybe have a teen themselves or can relate in some way. There were countless earth side angels and heaven sent angels lifting each one of us up. 🕊️ I wish I could take the pain away. Drew (his dad) spoke and emphasized that YOU MATTER. I think the word that comes to mind is grace. I hope that each one of us can give each other grace. Love all no matter what. Stop judging. Show kindness and remember that everyone is fighting their own fight whether we see it or not. 🤍 B, I love you. Fly high and take care of Rylee until I get there. 🕊️
